This paper discusses the concept of support constraints in machine learning, specifically in support vector machines. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses logical constraints expressed by Łukasiewicz logic, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The paper also provides theoretical results, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Finally, the paper discusses criteria for removing unnecessary constraints, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
